profile_positions.description:
On behalf of WASTE I act as project manager of the UNICEF-WASTE partnership that aims to improved sanitation services that are offered in Ulónguè, Homoine, Morrumbene and Jangamo towns, through a system of local stakeholders (local governments, private sector, households and financiers) that provide sustainable sanitation products and services, and an approach that is replicable at a larger scale in Mozambique.

In this partnership WASTE is responsible for the:

- Development a local support structure to assist entrepreneurs starting, sustaining and scaling their 
sanitation business;
- Development and implementation of alternative financing mechanisms for households and entrepreneurs;
- Training of AIAS (national responsible institute for urban sanitation) and local governments in implementing the Diamond Approach to facilitate the expansion and scaling up of sanitation services in the towns and surrounding areas.
